libsiot (0.4.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Add a decorator for range limited buffers in a stream (e.g. for protocols
    which limit data fields by length).

 -- Caoimhe Chaos <caoimhechaos@protonmail.com>  Thu, 09 May 2013 21:52:04 +0200

libsiot (0.3.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Stop accepting 0 as a size for unix socket buffers, handle it by resizing
    the buffer to 65536 just like in OpenSSL. (Fixes libhttp-server for HTTP
    traffic.)

 -- Caoimhe Chaos <caoimhechaos@protonmail.com>  Wed, 08 May 2013 00:44:37 +0200

libsiot (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Redo all of the locking to make SSL connections work properly (they're more
    prone to race conditions).
  * Add a separate thread for reaping closed connections.

 -- Caoimhe Chaos <caoimhechaos@protonmail.com>  Tue, 07 May 2013 19:18:13 +0200

libsiot (0.2.3-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Added a way to wrap connections in decorators before they're used in the
    server
  * Added a decorator which requires to ack data before it stops being
    returned by Receive().

 -- Caoimhe Chaos <caoimhechaos@protonmail.com>  Tue, 26 Mar 2013 01:28:32 +0100

